    <note>Song(2) Dao [3803] The Song Di [2124], who I have identified as his brother and XCB, 221.25b identifies as his brother, was the brother of a Luoyang, Dao, who was a painter with the zi of Gongda, whereas this Dao's zi was Shuda. Both earned the jinshi and I am assuming that they were the same person. Although Fan Chunren mentions nothing about his skill as a painter, it is unlikely that there were two sets of brothers, Dao and Di, both living in Luoyang at the same time. XCB, 221.25b, 26a; Fan Chunren, WJ, 13.4a-7b. CBD, 1, 750.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1071:  Apt. Tong Tiju Sanmen baibo nianyun (Co-superintendent of Sanmen rapids transport)</note>
